# Additional Implementation Patterns

For core conventions, see:
- `09-db-conventions.mdc` — table naming, column naming, data types
- `10-function-conventions.mdc` — function naming, BFF patterns, response format
- `11-auth-conventions.mdc` — auth patterns, merchant resolution, roles

This file covers topics not in those rules.

## Views

- Regular views: `v_<domain>_<purpose>` (real-time, on-demand)
- Materialized views: `mv_<domain>_<purpose>` (cached, requires explicit refresh)
- BFF views: `bff_<purpose>` (enriched for frontend)
- Views inherit RLS from underlying tables; materialized views need SECURITY DEFINER wrapper functions

## Anon Role Policies

Anon role policies must check `get_current_merchant_id() IS NOT NULL` to prevent unauthenticated access.

## CS Module — Cross-Domain Rules

### Shared Workflow Tables
`workflow_master`, `workflow_node`, `workflow_edge`, `workflow_trigger`, `workflow_log` — shared by loyalty and CS. Use `domain` column to filter: `'loyalty'` or `'cs'`.

### Cross-Domain Access
When CS functions need loyalty data (user tier, points, tags):
- Read via existing loyalty functions — look them up in INDEX_FUNCTION.md
- NEVER write to loyalty tables directly from CS functions
- For writes: use bridge functions that route through existing loyalty logic (e.g., `post_wallet_transaction` for points, `fn_execute_amp_action` for tags)
